No evidence of pulmonary edema . Degenerative changes in the thoracic spine with no obvious vertebral compression fractures . Osteopenia .

No pneumothorax has developed . Previously described marked cardiomegaly persists . Cardiac contours , however , are partially obscured by the high positioned diaphragms and bilateral pleural effusions which are more marked on the left than the right . No new parenchymal infiltrates are identified . In comparison with the portable examination of ___ a mild progression of the previously described CHF pattern and pleural effusions has occurred . FINDINGS : PA and lateral chest views were obtained with patient in upright position . Analysis is performed in direct comparison with the next preceding similar study of ___ . No evidence of acute new pulmonary infiltrates or advanced CHF in comparison with preceding studies .
